@node "Usage" "Usage of RandomCopy"

  RandomCopy is an little CLI/Shell command for
  all AMIGA (forever) computers.

  The syntax of RandomCopy:

  1) RandomCopy ?

     This syntax will cause RandomCopy to show
     you a short information about itself.

  2) RandomCopy <ListFile> <TargetFile>

     This filename <ListFile> defines an ASCII-file which contains
     a list with a desired number of filenames.
     Every line in the file may contain only one filename.

     If RandomCopy gets started it selects a random filename
     out of this list. If the selected file exists it will be
     copied to the filename <TargetFile>.

     Example:
     "RandomCopy sys:picturelist.txt ram:PictureX"
     This will copy a random file out of the list in "sys:picturelist.txt"
     to the file "ram:PictureX". The selected source file will
     leave untouched.
     The list "sys:picturelist.txt" could look like this:

     work:pictures/ilbm/girlpic1
     work:pictures/ilbm/girlpic2
     work:pictures/gif/parrot.gif
     sdh1:pics/explosion.pic






